data.enText: making it easy, possible or likely for sth to happen
data.chText: 使容易（或有可能）发生的

data.enText: Chairs in rows are not as conducive to discussion as chairs arranged in a circle.
data.chText: 椅子成排摆放不如成圈摆放便于讨论。

means: 使容易(或有可能)发生的

example: working conditions are not conducive to productivity
the seaport was a contributing factor in the growth of the city

example.ex: Make your bedroom as conducive to sleep as possible...
example.tran: 尽量把卧室布置得适宜睡眠。

example.ex: Sometimes the home environment just isn't conducive to reading.
example.tran: 有时候，家里的环境确实不适合看书。

gramarinfo.label: usu v-link ADJ, usu ADJ <l>to</l> n/-ing

value.def: If one thing is conducive to another thing, it makes the other thing likely to happen.
